  "prob_desc_output_spec": "The first line should contain a single integer k — the number of integers encrypting the row, e.g. the number of groups of black squares in the row. The second line should contain k integers, encrypting the row, e.g. corresponding to sizes of groups of consecutive black squares in the order from left to right.",
  "source_code": "#include<stdio.h>\n#include<string.h>\nint main()\n{\n\tlong long i, j, k;\n\tlong long n;\n\tlong long arr[10000];\n\tchar str[1000];\n\tscanf(\"%lld\", &n);\n\tscanf(\"%s\", str);\n\tlong long len=strlen(str);\n\tlong long maj_count=0,count=0,flag=0;\n\tk=0;\n\tfor(i=0;str[i]!='\\0';i++)\n\t{\n\t\tif(str[i]=='B')\n\t\t\tcount++;\n\t\tif((str[i]=='W' &&  str[i-1]=='B') || (str[i]=='B' && i==len-1))\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tflag=1;\n\t\t//\tprintf(\"%c\",str[i]);\n\t\t\tarr[k]=count;\n\t\t\tk++;\n\t\t\tcount=0;\n\t\t\tmaj_count++;\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t\n\tprintf(\"%lld\\n\",maj_count);\n\tfor(i=0;i<k-1 && arr[i]!=0;i++)\n\t\tprintf(\"%lld \",arr[i]);\n\tif(flag==1)\n\t\tprintf(\"%lld\\n\",arr[k-1]);\n//\tprintf(\"%lld\\n\",k);\n\treturn 0;\n}\n",
